{
  "text": "3) Carbon Monoxide Measurement was undertaken on a random number of schools (2 HPS, 2 public non HPS, and 4 private schools) using Exhaled Breath CO Monitor. CO measurement for students was done (N = 419), where a value of more than 10 ppm indicated that the subject was a smoker [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "8022570"
